{"timestamp": "2026-05-26 17:36:29,404", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_validation_result", "line": 185, "message": "{\"timestamp\": \"2026-05-26T17:36:29.404715\", \"task_id\": \"unknown\", \"task_objective\": \"Implement module to analyze job description and extract required skills, responsibilities, and criteria\", \"result\": \"```python\\n[\\n    \\\"def analyze_job_description(job_description):\\\",\\n    \\\"    \\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"Analyzes the job description and extracts required skills, responsibilities, and criteria.\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"    required_skills = []\\\",\\n    \\\"    responsibilities = []\\\",\\n    \\\"    criteria = {}\\\",\\n    \\\"    # Placeholder for actual implementation using NLP or keyword extraction techniques\\\",\\n    \\\"    # Example:\\\",\\n    \\\"    # - Extract skills using NLP models (spaCy, NLTK) or regular expressions\\\",\\n    \\\"    # - Identify key respo...\", \"validation_type\": \"text\", \"status\": \"failed\", \"feedback\": \"here are some feedbacks:\\n- The implementation is only a placeholder and lacks any real parsing logic.\\n- It doesn’t handle structured sections (like “Skills:”, “Responsibilities:”, “Requirements:”) often found in job descriptions.\\n- It doesn’t generalize beyond a few hard-coded keywords.\\n- We should provide a basic but working extraction using regular expressions and simple heuristics.\\n\\nhere are the changes:\\n```python\\n[\\n    \\\"import re\\\",\\n    \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"def analyze_job_description(job_description: str):\\\",\\n    \\\"    \\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"Analyzes the job description text and extracts required skills, responsibilities, and criteria sections.\\\",\\n    \\\"    Returns three lists: skills, responsibilities, and criteria.\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"    # Define section headings and regex patterns\\\",\\n    \\\"    section_patterns = {\\\",\\n    \\\"        'skills': r'(?:required skills|skills required|skills):?\\\\\\\\s*(.*?)\\\\\\\\n{2,}',\\\",\\n    \\\"        'responsibilities': r'(?:responsibilities|key responsibilities):?\\\\\\\\s*(.*?)\\\\\\\\n{2,}',\\\",\\n    \\\"        'criteria': r'(?:requirements|qualifications|criteria):?\\\\\\\\s*(.*?)\\\\\\\\n{2,}'\\\",\\n    \\\"    }\\\",\\n    \\\"    results = {'skills': [], 'responsibilities': [], 'criteria': []}\\\",\\n    \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"    # Normalize whitespace\\\",\\n    \\\"    text = job_description + '\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n'\\\",\\n    \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"    for section, pattern in section_patterns.items():\\\",\\n    \\\"        match = re.search(pattern, text, re.IGNORECASE | re.DOTALL)\\\",\\n    \\\"        if match:\\\",\\n    \\\"            block = match.group(1).strip()\\\",\\n    \\\"            # Split by lines or commas\\\",\\n    \\\"            lines = re.split(r'[\\\\\\\\n•\\\\\\\\-]+', block)\\\",\\n    \\\"            for item in lines:\\\",\\n    \\\"                item = item.strip(' :;,.')\\\",\\n    \\\"                if item:\\\",\\n    \\\"                    results[section].append(item)\\\",\\n    \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"    # Fallback keyword-based extraction if sections not found\\\",\\n    \\\"    if not results['skills']:\\\",\\n    \\\"        keywords = ['Python', 'Java', 'communication', 'SQL', 'AWS']\\\",\\n    \\\"        for kw in keywords:\\\",\\n    \\\"            if re.search(r'\\\\\\\\b' + re.escape(kw) + r'\\\\\\\\b', text):\\\",\\n    \\\"                results['skills'].append(kw)\\\",\\n    \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"    return results['skills'], results['responsibilities'], results['criteria']\\\",\\n]\\n```\"}"}
{"timestamp": "2026-05-26 17:36:31,692", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_gpt_conversation", "line": 403, "message": "{\n  \"event_type\": \"gpt_conversation\",\n  \"task_id\": \"task_Implement email send\",\n  \"conversation_type\": \"task_re_execution\",\n  \"iteration\": 2,\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"system\",\n      \"content\": \"\\n# Role\\nYou are a task re-execution agent. Your role is to generate an improved outcome for the given task by carefully considering the provided context, downstream objectives, previous execution results, and feedback.\\n\\n# Objective & Steps:\\n\\n1. Apply Corrections and Enhancements:\\n   - Address major problems based on previous execution results, and feedback.\\n\\n2. Ensure Completeness:\\n   - Avoid placeholders or incomplete text.\\n   - Your output must meet all requirements of the task.\\n   - Include all necessary details so that the output is self-contained and can be directly used as input for downstream tasks.\\n\\n3. Avoid Repetition:\\n   - Do not repeat verbatim content from previous executions.\\n\\n4. Maintain Precision and Clarity:\\n   - Your output will be used as input for subsequent tasks; therefore, it must be comprehensive and precise.\\n   - **Output the answer only without any jusifications**\\n\\n\\n# Audience:\\nYour output will serve as an improved solution for the task and will undergo further validation and integration into the larger workflow.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": \"---\\n## VERSION 0\\n```python\\n[\\n    \\\"Analyze the job description\\\",\\n    \\\"Analyze the candidate resume\\\",\\n    \\\"Conduct technical interview\\\",\\n    \\\"Send emails as and when needed\\\",\\n    \\\"Score candidate responses\\\",\\n    \\\"Generate final evaluation report\\\"\\n]\\n```\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": \"---\\n## FEEDBACK to VERSION 0\\nhere are some feedbacks:\\n- The current output just repeats the overall workflow list; it does not implement the required email‐sending functionality.\\n- The task asks specifically for a Python code module to dispatch notifications and interview invites, which is missing.\\n- We need functions (e.g. `send_email`, `send_notification`, `send_interview_invite`) with SMTP configuration and error handling.\\n\\nhere are the changes:\\n```python\\nimport smtplib\\nfrom email.message import EmailMessage\\nfrom typing import List, Dict\\n\\nclass EmailSender:\\n    def __init__(self, smtp_server: str, smtp_port: int, username: str, password: str, use_tls: bool = True):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Initialize the email sender with SMTP server details.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        self.smtp_server = smtp_server\\n        self.smtp_port = smtp_port\\n        self.username = username\\n        self.password = password\\n        self.use_tls = use_tls\\n\\n    def send_email(self, recipient: str, subject: str, body: str) -> bool:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Sends a single email. Returns True if successful, False otherwise.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        try:\\n            msg = EmailMessage()\\n            msg[\\\"From\\\"] = self.username\\n            msg[\\\"To\\\"] = recipient\\n            msg[\\\"Subject\\\"] = subject\\n            msg.set_content(body)\\n\\n            with smtplib.SMTP(self.smtp_server, self.smtp_port) as server:\\n                if self.use_tls:\\n                    server.starttls()\\n                server.login(self.username, self.password)\\n                server.send_message(msg)\\n            print(f\\\"Email sent to {recipient} with subject '{subject}'\\\")\\n            return True\\n        except Exception as e:\\n            print(f\\\"Failed to send email to {recipient}: {e}\\\")\\n            return False\\n\\n    def send_notification(self, recipients: List[str], notification_subject: str, notification_body: str) -> Dict[str, bool]:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Send a generic notification email to multiple recipients.\\n        Returns a dict mapping each recipient to True/False based on success.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        results = {}\\n        for email in recipients:\\n            success = self.send_email(email, notification_subject, notification_body)\\n            results[email] = success\\n        return results\\n\\n    def send_interview_invite(self, candidate_email: str, candidate_name: str, interview_date: str, instructions: str) -> bool:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Send an interview invitation to a single candidate.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        subject = f\\\"Interview Invitation for {candidate_name}\\\"\\n        body = (\\n            f\\\"Hello {candidate_name},\\\\n\\\\n\\\"\\n            f\\\"You are invited to an interview on {interview_date}.\\\\n\\\"\\n            f\\\"Instructions:\\\\n{instructions}\\\\n\\\\n\\\"\\n            \\\"Please reply to confirm your availability.\\\\n\\\\n\\\"\\n            \\\"Best regards,\\\\n\\\"\\n            \\\"Recruitment Team\\\"\\n        )\\n        return self.send_email(candidate_email, subject, body)\\n\\n# Example usage\\nif __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n    smtp_config = {\\n        \\\"smtp_server\\\": \\\"smtp.example.com\\\",\\n        \\\"smtp_port\\\": 587,\\n        \\\"username\\\": \\\"recruiter@example.com\\\",\\n        \\\"password\\\": \\\"securepassword\\\",\\n        \\\"use_tls\\\": True\\n    }\\n\\n    email_sender = EmailSender(**smtp_config)\\n\\n    # Send a generic notification\\n    notifications = email_sender.send_notification(\\n        recipients=[\\\"applicant1@example.com\\\", \\\"applicant2@example.com\\\"],\\n        notification_subject=\\\"Application Received\\\",\\n        notification_body=\\\"Thank you for applying. We have received your application and will be in touch.\\\"\\n    )\\n    print(\\\"Notification results:\\\", notifications)\\n\\n    # Send an interview invite\\n    invite_success = email_sender.send_interview_invite(\\n        candidate_email=\\\"candidate@example.com\\\",\\n        candidate_name=\\\"Jane Doe\\\",\\n        interview_date=\\\"2024-07-01 10:00 AM\\\",\\n        instructions=\\\"Please join the Zoom meeting with the link provided in the calendar invite.\\\"\\n    )\\n    print(\\\"Interview invite sent:\\\", invite_success)\\n```\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"# **The Overall Goal**\\nYou are a workflow planning agent.\\nYour task is to:\\n-\\\"Analyze the job description\\\",\\n    \\\"Analyze the candidate resume\\\",\\n    \\\"Conduct technical interview\\\",\\n    \\\"Send emails as and when needed\\\",\\n    \\\"Score candidate responses\\\",\\n    \\\"Generate final evaluation report\\\"\\n\\nReturn the output as a Python list of strings.\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n---\\n# **Context from Upstream Tasks**\\nNo completed previous tasks context available.\\n\\n---\\n# **Downstream Tasks Objectives**\\nTask task3:\\n  Objective: Implement technical interview conductor module to present questions and capture responses\\nTask task5:\\n  Objective: Implement final evaluation report generator that compiles analysis, scores, and sends summary\\n\\n---\\n# **Current Task Requirements**\\nImplement email sending module to dispatch notifications and interview invites\\n\\n---\\n\\n# **Required Output Format**\\nPython code\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"gpt_response\": \"```python\\nimport smtplib\\nfrom email.message import EmailMessage\\nfrom typing import List, Dict\\n\\nclass EmailSender:\\n    def __init__(self, smtp_server: str, smtp_port: int, username: str, password: str, use_tls: bool = True):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Initialize the email sender with SMTP server details.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        self.smtp_server = smtp_server\\n        self.smtp_port = smtp_port\\n        self.username = username\\n        self.password = password\\n        self.use_tls = use_tls\\n\\n    def send_email(self, recipient: str, subject: str, body: str) -> bool:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Sends a single email. Returns True if successful, False otherwise.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        try:\\n            msg = EmailMessage()\\n            msg[\\\"From\\\"] = self.username\\n            msg[\\\"To\\\"] = recipient\\n            msg[\\\"Subject\\\"] = subject\\n            msg.set_content(body)\\n\\n            with smtplib.SMTP(self.smtp_server, self.smtp_port) as server:\\n                if self.use_tls:\\n                    server.starttls()\\n                server.login(self.username, self.password)\\n                server.send_message(msg)\\n            print(f\\\"Email sent to {recipient} with subject '{subject}'\\\")\\n            return True\\n        except Exception as e:\\n            print(f\\\"Failed to send email to {recipient}: {e}\\\")\\n            return False\\n\\n    def send_notification(self, recipients: List[str], notification_subject: str, notification_body: str) -> Dict[str, bool]:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Send a generic notification email to multiple recipients.\\n        Returns a dict mapping each recipient to True/False based on success.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        results = {}\\n        for email in recipients:\\n            success = self.send_email(email, notification_subject, notification_body)\\n            results[email] = success\\n        return results\\n\\n    def send_interview_invite(self, candidate_email: str, candidate_name: str, interview_date: str, instructions: str) -> bool:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Send an interview invitation to a single candidate.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        subject = f\\\"Interview Invitation for {candidate_name}\\\"\\n        body = (\\n            f\\\"Hello {candidate_name},\\\\n\\\\n\\\"\\n            f\\\"You are invited to an interview on {interview_date}.\\\\n\\\"\\n            f\\\"Instructions:\\\\n{instructions}\\\\n\\\\n\\\"\\n            \\\"Please reply to confirm your availability.\\\\n\\\\n\\\"\\n            \\\"Best regards,\\\\n\\\"\\n            \\\"Recruitment Team\\\"\\n        )\\n        return self.send_email(candidate_email, subject, body)\\n\\n# Example usage\\nif __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n    smtp_config = {\\n        \\\"smtp_server\\\": \\\"smtp.example.com\\\",\\n        \\\"smtp_port\\\": 587,\\n        \\\"username\\\": \\\"recruiter@example.com\\\",\\n        \\\"password\\\": \\\"securepassword\\\",\\n        \\\"use_tls\\\": True\\n    }\\n\\n    email_sender = EmailSender(**smtp_config)\\n\\n    # Send a generic notification\\n    notifications = email_sender.send_notification(\\n        recipients=[\\\"applicant1@example.com\\\", \\\"applicant2@example.com\\\"],\\n        notification_subject=\\\"Application Received\\\",\\n        notification_body=\\\"Thank you for applying. We have received your application and will be in touch.\\\"\\n    )\\n    print(\\\"Notification results:\\\", notifications)\\n\\n    # Send an interview invite\\n    invite_success = email_sender.send_interview_invite(\\n        candidate_email=\\\"candidate@example.com\\\",\\n        candidate_name=\\\"Jane Doe\\\",\\n        interview_date=\\\"2024-07-01 10:00 AM\\\",\\n        instructions=\\\"Please join the Zoom meeting with the link provided in the calendar invite.\\\"\\n    )\\n    print(\\\"Interview invite sent:\\\", invite_success)\\n```\\n\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-26T17:36:31.692313\"\n}"}
