skills based on importance in job description.\\\",\\n    \\\"Score candidate proficiency for each required skill.\\\",\\n    \\\"Calculate overall resume match score.\\\",\\n    \\\"Generate a report summarizing resume analysis and score.\\\",\\n    \\\"Highlight areas of strength and weakness based on job requirements.\\\",\\n    \\\"Store extracted information in structured format (e.g., JSON).\\\",\\n    \\\"Provide justification for the match score and identified strengths/weaknesses.\\\"\\n]\\n```\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": \"---\\n## FEEDBACK to VERSION 0\\nhere are some feedbacks:\\n- The current list focuses on resume parsing and scoring but omits parsing the **job description** itself, which is essential for mapping.\\n- It lacks steps for **normalizing** skills (synonyms, variants) and using **semantic matching** (e.g., embeddings) to catch non-exact matches.\\n- It does not explicitly link **each job requirement** to the corresponding resume evidence (i.e., detailed mapping).\\n- It could benefit from a step to **parse and structure job requirements** before comparison.\\n- We should add mention of using NLP libraries or models for improved semantic matching.\\n\\nhere are the changes:\\n```python\\n[\\n    \\\"Parse job description text to extract and structure requirements (skills, years, responsibilities).\\\",\\n    \\\"Normalize extracted job requirements (standardize terminology, handle synonyms and variants).\\\",\\n    \\\"Parse resume content (TXT, PDF) to plain text.\\\",\\n    \\\"Extract key resume elements: skills, experiences (with dates), education, and project descriptions.\\\",\\n    \\\"Normalize resume skills using the same taxonomy as job requirements.\\\",\\n    \\\"Perform exact match mapping between resume skills and job requirements.\\\",\\n    \\\"Perform semantic similarity matching (e.g., using word embeddings or pretrained language models) to catch related skills.\\\",\\n    \\\"For each requirement, collect all matching resume entries and quantify proficiency (years, project count, role level).\\\",\\n    \\\"Assign weights to job requirements based on importance from the job description.\\\",\\n    \\\"Calculate a per-requirement match score: weighted combination of exact and semantic match strengths.\\\",\\n    \\\"Aggregate per-requirement scores into an overall resume–job match score.\\\",\\n    \\\"Generate a detailed mapping report showing each job requirement, matched resume evidence, and individual scores.\\\",\\n    \\\"Highlight strengths (high-scoring requirements) and gaps (unmatched or low scores).\\\",\\n    \\\"Provide a JSON-serializable output with structured fields: requirements, matches, scores, overall_score.\\\",\\n    \\\"Log and store parsed data and final results for downstream processing.\\\"\\n]\\n```\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"# **The Overall Goal**\\nYou are a workflow planning agent.\\nYour task is to:\\n-\\\"Analyze the job description\\\",\\n    \\\"Analyze the candidate resume\\\",\\n    \\\"Conduct technical interview\\\",\\n    \\\"Send emails as and when needed\\\",\\n    \\\"Score candidate responses\\\",\\n    \\\"Generate final evaluation report\\\"\\n\\nReturn the output as a Python list of strings.\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n---\\n# **Context from Upstream Tasks**\\nNo completed previous tasks context available.\\n\\n---\\n# **Downstream Tasks Objectives**\\nTask task3:\\n  Objective: Implement technical interview conductor module to present questions and capture responses\\n\\n---\\n# **Current Task Requirements**\\nImplement module to analyze candidate resume and map experience to job requirements\\n\\n---\\n\\n# **Required Output Format**\\nPython code\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"gpt_response\": \"```python\\n[\\n    \\\"Parse job description text to extract and structure requirements (skills, years, responsibilities).\\\",\\n    \\\"Normalize extracted job requirements (standardize terminology, handle synonyms and variants).\\\",\\n    \\\"Parse resume content (TXT, PDF) to plain text.\\\",\\n    \\\"Extract key resume elements: skills, experiences (with dates), education, and project descriptions.\\\",\\n    \\\"Normalize resume skills using the same taxonomy as job requirements.\\\",\\n    \\\"Perform exact match mapping between resume skills and job requirements.\\\",\\n    \\\"Perform semantic similarity matching (e.g., using word embeddings or pretrained language models) to catch related skills.\\\",\\n    \\\"For each requirement, collect all matching resume entries and quantify proficiency (years, project count, role level).\\\",\\n    \\\"Assign weights to job requirements based on importance from the job description.\\\",\\n    \\\"Calculate a per-requirement match score: weighted combination of exact and semantic match strengths.\\\",\\n    \\\"Aggregate per-requirement scores into an overall resume–job match score.\\\",\\n    \\\"Generate a detailed mapping report showing each job requirement, matched resume evidence, and individual scores.\\\",\\n    \\\"Highlight strengths (high-scoring requirements) and gaps (unmatched or low scores).\\\",\\n    \\\"Provide a JSON-serializable output with structured fields: requirements, matches, scores, overall_score.\\\",\\n    \\\"Log and store parsed data and final results for downstream processing.\\\"\\n]\\n```\\n\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-26T17:36:32.508820\"\n}"}
{"timestamp": "2026-05-26 17:36:34,146", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_gpt_conversation", "line": 403, "message": "{\n  \"event_type\": \"gpt_conversation\",\n  \"task_id\": \"task_Implement module to \",\n  \"conversation_type\": \"task_re_execution\",\n  \"iteration\": 2,\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"system\",\n      \"content\": \"\\n# Role\\nYou are a task re-execution agent. Your role is to generate an improved outcome for the given task by carefully considering the provided context, downstream objectives, previous execution results, and feedback.\\n\\n# Objective & Steps:\\n\\n1. Apply Corrections and Enhancements:\\n   - Address major problems based on previous execution results, and feedback.\\n\\n2. Ensure Completeness:\\n   - Avoid placeholders or incomplete text.\\n   - Your output must meet all requirements of the task.\\n   - Include all necessary details so that the output is self-contained and can be directly used as input for downstream tasks.\\n\\n3. Avoid Repetition:\\n   - Do not repeat verbatim content from previous executions.\\n\\n4. Maintain Precision and Clarity:\\n   - Your output will be used as input for subsequent tasks; therefore, it must be comprehensive and precise.\\n   - **Output the answer only without any jusifications**\\n\\n\\n# Audience:\\nYour output will serve as an improved solution for the task and will undergo further validation and integration into the larger workflow.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": \"---\\n## VERSION 0\\n```python\\n[\\n    \\\"def analyze_job_description(job_description):\\\",\\n    \\\"    \\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"Analyzes the job description and extracts required skills, responsibilities, and criteria.\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"    required_skills = []\\\",\\n    \\\"    responsibilities = []\\\",\\n    \\\"    criteria = {}\\\",\\n    \\\"    # Placeholder for actual implementation using NLP or keyword extraction techniques\\\",\\n    \\\"    # Example:\\\",\\n    \\\"    # - Extract skills using NLP models (spaCy, NLTK) or regular expressions\\\",\\n    \\\"    # - Identify key responsibilities from the job description text\\\",\\n    \\\"    # - Extract criteria based on keywords like 'experience', 'education', 'certifications'\\\",\\n    \\\"    # Example implementation (replace with actual logic):\\\",\\n    \\\"    if 'Python' in job_description:\\\",\\n    \\\"        required_skills.append('Python')\\\",\\n    \\\"    if 'communication skills' in job_description:\\\",\\n    \\\"        required_skills.append('communication skills')\\\",\\n    \\\"    if 'software development' in job_description:\\\",\\n    \\\"        responsibilities.append('software development')\\\",\\n    \\\"    if 'teamwork' in job_description:\\\",\\n    \\\"        responsibilities.append('teamwork')\\\",\\n    \\\"    if 'years of experience' in job_description:\\\",\\n    \\\"        criteria['experience'] = 'minimum X years'\\\",\\n    \\\"    if 'degree' in job_description:\\\",\\n    \\\"        criteria['education'] = 'Bachelor\\\\'s degree or higher'\\\",\\n    \\\"    return required_skills, responsibilities, criteria\\\"\\n]\\n```\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": \"---\\n## FEEDBACK to VERSION 0\\nhere are some feedbacks:\\n- The implementation is only a placeholder and lacks any real parsing logic.\\n- It doesn’t handle structured sections (like “Skills:”, “Responsibilities:”, “Requirements:”) often found in job descriptions.\\n- It doesn’t generalize beyond a few hard-coded keywords.\\n- We should provide a basic but working extraction using regular expressions and simple heuristics.\\n\\nhere are the changes:\\n```python\\n[\\n    \\\"import re\\\",\\n    \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"def analyze_job_description(job_description: str):\\\",\\n    \\\"    \\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"Analyzes the job description text and extracts required skills, responsibilities, and criteria sections.\\\",\\n    \\\"    Returns three lists: skills, responsibilities, and criteria.\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"    # Define section headings and regex patterns\\\",\\n    \\\"    section_patterns = {\\\",\\n    \\\"        'skills': r'(?:required skills|skills required|skills):?\\\\\\\\s*(.*?)\\\\\\\\n{2,}',\\\",\\n    \\\"        'responsibilities': r'(?:responsibilities|key responsibilities):?\\\\\\\\s*(.*?)\\\\\\\\n{2,}',\\\",\\n    \\\"        'criteria': r'(?:requirements|qualifications|criteria):?\\\\\\\\s*(.*?)\\\\\\\\n{2,}'\\\",\\n    \\\"    }\\\",\\n    \\\"    results = {'skills': [], 'responsibilities': [], 'criteria': []}\\\",\\n    \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"    # Normalize whitespace\\\",\\n    \\\"    text = job_description + '\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n'\\\",\\n    \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"    for section, pattern in section_patterns.items():\\\",\\n    \\\"        match = re.search(pattern, text, re.IGNORECASE | re.DOTALL)\\\",\\n    \\\"        if match:\\\",\\n    \\\"            block = match.group(1).strip()\\\",\\n    \\\"            # Split by lines or commas\\\",\\n    \\\"            lines = re.split(r'[\\\\\\\\n•\\\\\\\\-]+', block)\\\",\\n    \\\"            for item in lines:\\\",\\n    \\\"                item = item.strip(' :;,.')\\\",\\n    \\\"                if item:\\\",\\n    \\\"                    results[section].append(item)\\\",\\n    \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"    # Fallback keyword-based extraction if sections not found\\\",\\n    \\\"    if not results['skills']:\\\",\\n    \\\"        keywords = ['Python', 'Java', 'communication', 'SQL', 'AWS']\\\",\\n    \\\"        for kw in keywords:\\\",\\n    \\\"            if re.search(r'\\\\\\\\b' + re.escape(kw) + r'\\\\\\\\b', text):\\\",\\n    \\\"                results['skills'].append(kw)\\\",\\n    \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"    return results['skills'], results['responsibilities'], results['criteria']\\\",\\n]\\n```\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"# **The Overall Goal**\\nYou are a workflow planning agent.\\nYour task is to:\\n-\\\"Analyze the job description\\\",\\n    \\\"Analyze the candidate resume\\\",\\n    \\\"Conduct technical interview\\\",\\n    \\\"Send emails as and when needed\\\",\\n    \\\"Score candidate responses\\\",\\n    \\\"Generate final evaluation report\\\"\\n\\nReturn the output as a Python list of strings.\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n---\\n# **Context from Upstream Tasks**\\nNo completed previous tasks context available.\\n\\n---\\n# **Downstream Tasks Objectives**\\nTask task3:\\n  Objective: Implement technical interview conductor module to present questions and capture responses\\n\\n---\\n# **Current Task Requirements**\\nImplement module to analyze job description and extract required skills, responsibilities, and criteria\\n\\n---\\n\\n# **Required Output Format**\\nPython code\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"gpt_response\": \"```python\\nimport re\\n\\ndef analyze_job_description(job_description: str):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Analyzes the job description text and extracts required skills, responsibilities, and criteria sections.\\n    Returns a dictionary with three keys: 'skills', 'responsibilities', and 'criteria', each containing a list of strings.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    # Define section headings and regex patterns\\n    section_patterns = {\\n        'skills': r'(?:required skills|skills required|skills|technical skills):?\\\\\\\\s*(.*?)(?=\\\\\\\\n{2,}|\\\\Z)',\\n        'responsibilities': r'(?:responsibilities|key responsibilities|job duties):?\\\\\\\\s*(.*?)(?=\\\\\\\\n{2,}|\\\\Z)',\\n        'criteria': r'(?:requirements|qualifications|criteria|experience needed):?\\\\\\\\s*(.*?)(?=\\\\\\\\n{2,}|\\\\Z)'\\n    }\\n    results = {'skills': [], 'responsibilities': [], 'criteria': []}\\n\\n    # Normalize whitespace\\n    text = job_description + '\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n'\\n\\n    for section, pattern in section_patterns.items():\\n        match = re.search(pattern, text, re.IGNORECASE | re.DOTALL)\\n        if match:\\n            block = match.group(1).strip()\\n            # Split by lines or common delimiters\\n            lines = re.split(r'[\\\\\\\\n•\\\\\\\\-]+', block)\\n            for item in lines:\\n                item = item.strip(' :;,.').replace(\\\"*\\\", \\\"\\\")\\n                if item:\\n                    results[section].append(item)\\n\\n    # Fallback keyword-based extraction if sections are sparse or not found, focusing on skills\\n    if not results['skills']:\\n        keywords = ['Python', 'Java', 'communication', 'SQL', 'AWS', 'JavaScript', 'C++', 'C#', 'React', 'Angular', 'Node.js', 'Data Analysis', 'Machine Learning', 'Deep Learning', 'Cloud Computing', 'Project Management', 'Testing', 'DevOps'] # Expanded keyword list\\n        for kw in keywords:\\n            if re.search(r'\\\\\\\\b' + re.escape(kw) + r'\\\\\\\\b', text, re.IGNORECASE):\\n                results['skills'].append(kw)\\n\\n    return results['skills'], results['responsibilities'], results['criteria']\\n```\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-26T17:36:34.146805\"\n}"}
