{"timestamp": "2026-05-26 17:37:07,331", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_gpt_conversation", "line": 403, "message": "{\n  \"event_type\": \"gpt_conversation\",\n  \"task_id\": \"task_2\",\n  \"conversation_type\": \"task_execution\",\n  \"iteration\": 1,\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"system\",\n      \"content\": \"\\n# Role:\\nHelp me produce a precise and detailed solution for the given task. Follow these instructions exactly:\\n\\n# Objective & Steps:\\n1. Ensure Completeness:\\n   - Avoid placeholders or incomplete text.\\n   - Your output must meet all requirements of the task.\\n   - Include all necessary details so that the output is self-contained and can be directly used as input for downstream tasks.\\n\\n2. Maintain Precision and Clarity:\\n   - Your output will be used as input for subsequent tasks; therefore, it must be comprehensive and precise.\\n   - **Output the answer only without any jusifications**\\n\\n3. Avoid Repetition:\\n   - Do not repeat verbatim any content from previous tasks.\\n   - Ensure your output is original and adds value to the workflow.\\n\\n\\n\\n# Audience:\\nYour output will be used as a solution for the given task, it will be used in the later validation and intergration process.\\n\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"# **The Overall Goal**\\nYou are a workflow planning agent.\\nYour task is to:\\n-\\\"Analyze the job description\\\",\\n    \\\"Analyze the candidate resume\\\",\\n    \\\"Conduct technical interview\\\",\\n    \\\"Send emails as and when needed\\\",\\n    \\\"Score candidate responses\\\",\\n    \\\"Generate final evaluation report\\\"\\n\\nReturn the output as a Python list of strings.\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n---\\n# **Context from Upstream Tasks**\\nTask task3:\\n  Objective: Implement technical interview conductor module to present questions and capture responses\\n  Result: ```python\\nclass TechnicalInterviewConductor:\\n    def __init__(self, questions):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Initializes the interview conductor with a list of questions.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        self.questions = questions\\n        self.responses = {}\\n\\n    def present_question(self, question_number):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Presents a question to the candidate and captures the response.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        if 1 <= question_number <= len(self.questions):\\n            question = self.questions[question_number - 1]\\n            print(f\\\"Question {question_number}: {question}\\\")\\n            response = input(\\\"Your answer: \\\")  # Capture response via console input\\n            self.responses[question] = response\\n            return True\\n        else:\\n            print(\\\"Invalid question number.\\\")\\n            return False\\n\\n    def get_response(self, question):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Returns the candidate's response to a specific question.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        return self.responses.get(question, None)\\n\\n    def conduct_interview(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Conducts the entire interview, presenting each question sequentially.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        for i in range(1, len(self.questions) + 1):\\n            self.present_question(i)\\n\\n    def get_all_responses(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Returns all captured responses as a dictionary.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        return self.responses\\n\\n# Example Usage\\nif __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n    sample_questions = [\\n        \\\"Explain the concept of polymorphism in object-oriented programming.\\\",\\n        \\\"Describe the difference between a stack and a queue.\\\",\\n        \\\"What are the advantages of using a relational database?\\\",\\n        \\\"How does garbage collection work in Python?\\\",\\n        \\\"Explain the concept of recursion and provide an example.\\\"\\n    ]\\n\\n    interviewer = TechnicalInterviewConductor(sample_questions)\\n    interviewer.conduct_interview()\\n\\n    all_responses = interviewer.get_all_responses()\\n    print(\\\"\\\\nAll Responses:\\\")\\n    for question, answer in all_responses.items():\\n        print(f\\\"Question: {question}\\\\nAnswer: {answer}\\\\n\\\")\\n```\\n\\n---\\n# **Downstream Tasks Objectives**\\nTask task5:\\n  Objective: Implement final evaluation report generator that compiles analysis, scores, and sends summary\\n\\n---\\n# **Current Task Requirements**\\nImplement scoring module to evaluate candidate responses against criteria\\n\\n---\\n\\n# **Required Output Format**\\nPython code\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"gpt_response\": \"```python\\nclass ScoringModule:\\n    def __init__(self, criteria):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Initializes the scoring module with the evaluation criteria.\\n        Criteria should be a dictionary where keys are aspects to evaluate\\n        and values are the corresponding weights.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        self.criteria = criteria\\n\\n    def score_response(self, question, response):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Scores the candidate's response to a specific question based on predefined criteria.\\n        This is a placeholder for a more sophisticated scoring mechanism.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        score = 0\\n        # Example scoring logic (replace with actual evaluation logic)\\n        if response:\\n            score += self.criteria.get(\\\"Completeness\\\", 0) if \\\"completeness\\\" in question.lower() else 0\\n            score += self.criteria.get(\\\"Correctness\\\", 0) if \\\"correct\\\" in question.lower() or \\\"accuracy\\\" in question.lower() else 0\\n            score += self.criteria.get(\\\"Clarity\\\", 0)\\n        return score\\n\\n    def calculate_total_score(self, responses):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Calculates the total score for all responses.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        total_score = 0\\n        for question, response in responses.items():\\n            total_score += self.score_response(question, response)\\n        return total_score\\n\\n    def generate_feedback(self, question, response, score):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Generates feedback based on the score.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        if score > 0:\\n            return f\\\"Good attempt on question: {question}.\\\"\\n        else:\\n            return f\\\"Needs improvement on question: {question}.\\\"\\n\\n# Example Usage\\nif __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n    # Define evaluation criteria with weights\\n    evaluation_criteria = {\\n        \\\"Completeness\\\": 0.3,\\n        \\\"Correctness\\\": 0.5,\\n        \\\"Clarity\\\": 0.2\\n    }\\n\\n    scorer = ScoringModule(evaluation_criteria)\\n\\n    # Sample responses (replace with actual responses from the interview)\\n    sample_responses = {\\n        \\\"Explain the concept of polymorphism in object-oriented programming.\\\": \\\"Polymorphism is when one object can take on many forms.\\\",\\n        \\\"Describe the difference between a stack and a queue.\\\": \\\"A stack is LIFO, and a queue is FIFO.\\\",\\n        \\\"What are the advantages of using a relational database?\\\": \\\"They are structured.\\\",\\n        \\\"How does garbage collection work in Python?\\\": \\\"It automatically frees up memory.\\\",\\n        \\\"Explain the concept of recursion and provide an example.\\\": \\\"Recursion is when a function calls itself.\\\"\\n    }\\n\\n    # Calculate total score\\n    total_score = scorer.calculate_total_score(sample_responses)\\n    print(f\\\"Total Score: {total_score}\\\")\\n\\n    # Generate feedback for each response\\n    for question, response in sample_responses.items():\\n        score = scorer.score_response(question, response)\\n        feedback = scorer.generate_feedback(question, response, score)\\n        print(f\\\"Question: {question}\\\\nResponse: {response}\\\\nScore: {score}\\\\nFeedback: {feedback}\\\\n\\\")\\n```\",\n  \"timestamp\